name: Aggie Fish Club
description:
Aggie Fish Club is an organization dedicated to the involvement of freshmen in Texas A&M University. Through weekly meetings, influential speakers, committee projects, Buddy Huddle activities, and leadership retreats, the freshmen are provided opportunities to grow as individuals, students, and Aggie leaders. Aggie Fish Club serves as a support system to the freshmen and encourages development through positive reinforcement, mentors, and friendship. AFC also focuses on the importance of Texas A&M history and tradition, while giving freshmen the opportunity to experience the Aggie Spirit.

 

Feel free to find more information regarding Aggie Fish Club at our official website aggiefishclub.squarespace.com
summary: Aggie Fish Club is an organization dedicated to the involvement of freshmen in Texas A&M University. AFC achieves this goal through emphasizing growth in each of our three pillars: leadership, service, and social.
